<h2><i>Daily (Olympia) Olympian</i></h2>
</center>

<center>1895: August 12</center>

<br>
 Mark Twain entertained a fair sized audience at the theater
Saturday night. His recitations and stories were greatly enjoyed
and applauded. He left for Tacoma yesterday, via the Olympia &amp;
Tumwater, Port Townsend Southern and Northern Pacific.

